During National Veterans Small Business Week, the article recognizes the contributions of veterans who have served in the military and now own small businesses. It highlights the courage and tenacity of these veterans in defending the nation and their continued contribution to its strength and prosperity. The article states that nearly 1 in 10 businesses in the United States is owned by a veteran, generating over $1 trillion in sales and employing more than 5 million people annually. The administration is committed to supporting these veterans and has implemented measures to cut regulations, provide tax cuts, and enhance access to capital for veteran-owned businesses. The article emphasizes the critical role that veteran-owned businesses play in the economy and expresses gratitude towards veterans for their service.